          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Collaborative Filtering",
          "Learning Paths",
          "100 undergraduate students",
          "-",
          "Learner-Activity Record\nActivity Metadata",
          "The knowledge graphs are built using entity types and relationships.\n\nLatent representations are created using Random-Walk",
          "Graph Edges are extended by interactions. \n\n",
          "Authors include bias parameters p and q to balance local/global walks\n\n- Skipgrams are used to create effiicient node representations",
          "Top-N learning activities",
          "{User Experience: 0.72, Effectiveness: 0.76, Impact on Learning: 0.7}",
          "The idea of the authors is to create a new path-based recommender system.\n\nActivities are captured by embeddings, which allows the identification of similar ones.\n\nProvides explainable recommendations via path tracing.\n\nResults on experiment with 100 students show that students who used the recommender have higher satisfaction when it comes to user experience, effectiveness and impact on learning.",
          "- Single domain.\n- No tests against other models.\n- Evaluated done only throughout a semester.\n- Limited scale - no exploration of the growth of the knowledge graph."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
